sub_title: Stagiair Deltares | MSc Candiate in Geoinformation Science and Earth Observation for Environmental Modelling and Management
summary:
My interest in problem-solving and the environment led me to pursue research  on topics related to water environments and natural catastrophes in South East Asia after graduating from my Bachelorâ€™s in Earth Sciences. After working on research for two years, I left for Europe to pursue my interest in applying geospatial technologies in studying the environment, and to satisfy my curiosity for the world beyond my country â€“ it has been amazing ðŸ˜Š  

I believe that discomfort is a catalyst for growth â€“ my commitment to growth compels me to actively create and seek out learning opportunities. For example, I joined an interdisciplinary research group at Pufendorf Institute of Advanced Studies to work on hydrosolidarity research â€“ a field that was still new to me then â€“ and published a peer-reviewed article as first author during the first year of my Masterâ€™s studies at Lund University. 

Curious to learn more about natural hazard risk and the use of artificial intelligence, I am currently working on data-driven modelling of spatio-temporal landslide susceptibility as part of my MSc thesis. 

In my free time, you may find me: reading (typically mystery, fantasy and personal development books), wandering the great outdoors, or scouting out delicious food.
